      <span class="eyebrow">A Word From the Principal</span>
      <h2>“To know oneself, to know the world, to know God.”</h2>
      <p>For more than six decades, Cognitio Lutheran Secondary School has stood beside the Wisdom Valley as a place of formation. We are not in the business of producing scores — we are in the business of forming people.</p>
      <p>Every student who walks through our doors is met with the same conviction: that learning is sacred work, and that knowledge without character is only half an education.</p>
      <p>Whether your child arrives drawn to mathematics, music, marine biology, or moral philosophy, our promise is the same — they will leave us with a sharper mind, a steadier conscience, and a wider horizon.</p>
      <p class="signature">— Dr. M. Kwok, Principal</p>
